"Biology: Discovering life"

"The book is divided into seven parts. Part 1 opens with an examination of biology and the nature of science. Part 2 immediately moves on to organisms and ecology. Part 3  presents Mendelian genetics and evolution. Part 4  presents the diversity of life in the format of an Evolutionary history of life. In part 5, Molecules of life, this book explores aspects of the connections between the material world and the living world. Part 6 examine the central role of bioenergetics and molecular biology in the study of plants, and to connect plants to the rest of the living world. Part 7 covers the field of organismal physiology from basic concepts of homeostasis through animal behavior"
